# CMake Conventions

## General
- Specify `cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.20)` or higher
- Use modern CMake: `target_*` commands over global `include_directories`/`add_definitions`
- Prefer imported/aliased targets over raw library names
- Split cmake files responsibillities into a cmake folder

## Style
- Use lowercase cmake commands (`add_library`, not `ADD_LIBRARY`)
- Quote all variable expansions in conditionals: `if("${VAR}" STREQUAL "value")`
- Group logically: options, dependencies, sources, target properties
